24
00:01:44,593 --> 00:01:50,976
Just in summary, the demolition delay process is a two-step process once paperwork is submitted.

25
00:01:51,457 --> 00:01:59,862
First step is to determine significance, and by definition, that means any building that's listed on the National Register of Historic Places

26
00:02:00,622 --> 00:02:25,910
any building that's listed on the Massachusetts Register of Historic Places, or any building that was built 75 years or older, which is determined by the commission to be a significant building as provided by subsection 7048-78D, either because it is importantly associated with one or more historic persons or events, or with the broad architectural, cultural, political, economic, or social history of the city or the Commonwealth,

27
00:02:26,570 --> 00:02:39,075
or it is historically or architecturally important in terms of period, style, method of building construction, or association with an important architect or builder, either by itself or in the context of a group of buildings.

28
00:02:39,836 --> 00:02:41,296
So way back in 2019,

29
00:02:47,626 --> 00:03:00,218
